description: "This mid-18th century map of Asia features a drawing of religious imagery: Asian people are seen making offerings to two figures, including the Greek god Poseidon (or the Roman god Neptune), and kneeling as cherubs descend from the sky."
title: "India orientalis, cum adjacentibus insulis nova delineatione ob oculos polita / per Matthaeum Seutter, S.C.M. Geogr. August."
